'''custom_town_number''' is a variable of Openttd.cfg file:

Specifies the exact number of towns on a new map, if the [[Main/en/Number towns|number_towns]] variable has got the value "4" (custom), or, if in the game, in the ''World Generation'' window ''Custom'' is selected at the setting ''No. of towns''.

<pre>
[game_creation]
custom_town_number = 1
</pre>

'''Valid options:''' [ 1 <= n <= 5000 ]

'''Default:''' 1


